Santander UK, the London-based subsidiary of Spanish banking group Banco Santander, S.A.., manages its affairs autonomously and is run by a local management team. Santander UK takes deposits in the UK and lends only to UK businesses and individuals. 

Santander Corporate &… MoreSantander UK, the London-based subsidiary of Spanish banking group Banco Santander, S.A.., manages its affairs autonomously and is run by a local management team. Santander UK takes deposits in the UK and lends only to UK businesses and individuals. 

Santander Corporate & Commercial Banking operates through 35 regional corporate business centres located across the UK, each providing banking support to medium and large business who require a relationship managed service and have more comprehensive banking, international business or larger lending needs. Corporate Banking team focuses on offering structured finance and tailored products and services to businesses with a turnover above £50 million.

Small to medium (SME) sized start-up or established businesses with straightforward banking needs and up to two directors, owners or partners are supported by the Business Banking team and network of Local Business Managers. Also aimed at the SME sector, Santander’s Breakthrough programme offers qualifying fast-growth companies funding and access to advice and networking.

Santander UK acquired Abbey Financial Markets in 2004 and subsequently re-branded the company as Santander Global Banking & Markets in 2007. 
• Maintains a £10M telecom expense management contract with BT.
• Maintains a £5M-£10M help desk management contract.

2013 and Earlier:
Santander UK is a London-based subsidiary of Spanish banking group Banco Santander, S.A.. The subsidiary, providing banking, financial services, and insurance, has… More• Maintains a £10M telecom expense management contract with BT.
• Maintains a £5M-£10M help desk management contract.

2013 and Earlier:
Santander UK is a London-based subsidiary of Spanish banking group Banco Santander, S.A.. The subsidiary, providing banking, financial services, and insurance, has over 1300 branches and over 25 million customers throughout the country.

Santander UK plc's IT department generally focuses on software and data center upgrades as well as information security. The company recently completed a data center transformation, which included virtualization projects.

The department is composed of two of its subsidiaries, Produban and ISBAN. ISBAN provides the company with software and systems integration services, while Produban provides IT infrastructure operations.
 





