Santander UK Group Holdings plc Key Developments

Bruce Carnegie-Brown to Step Down from the Board of Santander UK Group Holdings plc and Santander UK plc
May 22 17
Santander UK announced that Bruce Carnegie-Brown will be stepping down from the boards of the company on 1 June 2017. He will remain on the board of Banco Santander, S.A. as Vice Chairman and Lead Independent Director.


Santander UK Group Holdings plc, Q1 2017 Earnings Call, Apr 26, 2017
Apr 26 17
Santander UK Group Holdings plc, Q1 2017 Earnings Call, Apr 26, 2017


Santander UK Group Holdings plc Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Reports Impairment Losses on Loans and Advances for the First Quarter of 2017
Apr 26 17
Santander UK Group Holdings plc reported consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the period, the company reported net interest income of £940 million against £885 million a year ago. Total operating income was £1,205 million against £1,155 million a year ago. Profit before tax was £525 million against £532 million a year ago. Profit after tax for the period was £371 million against £378 million a year ago. Adjusted profit before tax was £582 million against £547 million a year ago. 

The company's impairment losses on loans and advances for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017 was £13 million against £13 million a year ago.


